%2C%20are%20aghast!%20Are%20young%20people%20cooked%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20perhaps%20it's%20OK%20to%20form%20new%20etiquette%20around%20phones.%20They%20haven't%20been%20around%20that%20long%2C%20anyway.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20answer%20the%20phone%2C%20do%20you%20say%20%26quot%3Bhello%26quot%3B%20or%20offer%20some%20sort%20of%20greeting%20right%20away%2C%20or%20do%20you%20expect%20the%20caller%20to%20initiate%20the%20conversation%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20over%20the%20age%20of%2028%2C%20my%20guess%20is%20you're%20confused%20by%20this%20question.%20Of%20course%20you%20say%20%26quot%3Bhello%26quot%3B%20when%20picking%20up%20the%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-office-emails-etiquette-changing-backfire-experts-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20generation%20raised%20in%20a%20post-landline%20universe%20%E2%80%94%20may%20disagree.%20They%20expect%20you%20%E2%80%94%20the%20person%20calling%20%E2%80%94%20to%20speak%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fjorilextera%2Fstatus%2F1943404451244454171%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eviral%20tweet%3C%2Fa%3E%20brought%20up%20this%20alarming%20etiquette%20divide.%20Someone%20who%20works%20in%20recruiting%20tweeted%20that%20she's%20noticed%20that%20when%20she%20calls%20Gen%20Z%20people%20(at%20their%20scheduled%20call%20time)%2C%20they%20often%20wait%20for%20her%20to%20speak%20first%20instead%20of%20saying%20%26quot%3Bhello.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20replies%20to%20her%20tweet%20were%20even%20more%20eye-opening%20%E2%80%94%20to%20me%2C%20anyway%3A%20Many%20young%20people%20agreed%20that%20it%20should%20be%20the%20%3Cem%3Ecaller's%3C%2Fem%3E%20responsibility%20to%20start%20speaking%20and%20offer%20a%20greeting%2C%20not%20the%20person%20answering%20the%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reasons%20these%20people%20gave%20settled%20into%20two%20main%20camps%3A%20The%20first%20is%20the%20huge%20amount%20of%20spam%20calls%20we%20all%20receive.%20(They%20%3Cem%3Eare%3C%2Fem%3E%20annoying.)%20Often%2C%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fhow-to-stop-spam-calls%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etelemarketers%20or%20robocalls%3C%2Fa%3E%20don't%20start%20until%20they%20hear%20someone%20say%20%26quot%3Bhello.%26quot%3B%20By%20remaining%20silent%20when%20you%20pick%20up%2C%20you%20can%20screen%20for%20a%20real%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2287887187-d89f-4a26-b3fe-8d8ffcba749a%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%20is%20wary%20of%20scammers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobocalls-deep-fakes-new-era-because-of-ai-experts-say-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESpam%20calls%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20a%20scourge%2C%20and%20it's%20hard%20to%20complain%20about%20anyone's%20tactics%20to%20avoid%20them.%20And%20yet%20%E2%80%A6%20there's%20gotta%20be%20a%20better%20way%2C%20right%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(I%20must%20note%20here%20that%20in%20my%20experience%20as%20someone%20who%20almost%20always%20answers%20unknown%20calls%2C%20since%20they%20may%20be%20work-related%2C%20if%20I%20say%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20Katie%26quot%3B%20instead%20of%20%26quot%3BHello%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20seems%20to%20stump%20the%20robocall%20software%2C%20which%20activates%20on%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Bhello.%26quot%3B%20I%20would%20recommend%20you%20all%20try%20this%20technique%2C%20but%20you'll%20have%20better%20results%20if%20you%20use%20your%20own%20name%20instead%20of%20%26quot%3BKatie.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20concern%20is%20that%20scammers%20might%20use%20a%20recording%20of%20your%20voice%20saying%20%26quot%3Bhello%26quot%3B%20to%20clone%20it%20for%20use%20in%20other%20scams.%20There%20is%20some%20real%20concern%20here.%20Marijus%20Briedis%2C%20chief%20technology%20officer%20at%20NordVPN%2C%20told%20me%20there's%20scant%20data%20on%20how%20often%20this%20happens%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20real%20thing.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20must%20respond%2C%20a%20neutral%2C%20non-personal%20greeting%20like%20'Who%20is%20this%3F'%20may%20be%20less%20useful%20for%20cloning%20because%20it%20is%20less%20emotionally%20expressive%20and%20less%20common%20as%20a%20voice%20sample%2C%26quot%3B%20Briedis%20said.%20(Personally%2C%20I%20think%20that's%20more%20rude%20than%20just%20silently%20breathing%20into%20the%20receiver%2C%20but%20hey.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22895dd2ab-124a-4899-ad0d-78861191c4e4%5C%22%3EEtiquette%20is%20changing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20reason%20some%20people%20are%20avoiding%20the%20%26quot%3Bhello%26quot%3B%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20generational%20difference%20in%20etiquette.%20Some%20young%20people%20simply%20believe%20that%20if%20you're%20the%20one%20who%20is%20calling%2C%20%3Cem%3Eyou%3C%2Fem%3E%20should%20initiate%20the%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20makes%20your%20blood%20pressure%20start%20to%20rise%2C%20like%20it%20does%20with%20me%2C%20let's%20take%20a%20deep%20breath%20together%20and%20try%20to%20think%20about%20this%20kindly.%20Are%20young%20people%20hopelessly%20adrift%20in%20society%2C%20untethered%20from%20being%20capable%20of%20the%20most%20basic%20elements%20of%20communication%3F%20Is%20this%20perhaps%20related%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bso-called%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-gen-z-stare-tiktok-examples-workplace-communication-skills-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%20stare%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20where%20young%20people%20in%20customer%20service%20situations%20blankly%20stare%20back%20at%20you%20(or%20avoid%20eye%20contact%2C%20wordlessly)%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20saying%20it's%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20that.%20I%20think%20that%20saying%20%26quot%3Bhello%26quot%3B%20when%20you%20answer%20the%20phone%20is%20normal%2C%20commonly%20accepted%20social%20etiquette%2C%20and%20not%20doing%20it%20can%20be%20slightly%20confusing%20for%20a%20caller.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20because%20something%20used%20to%20be%20common%20etiquette%20doesn't%20mean%20it%20has%20to%20stay%20that%20way.%20The%20telephone%20is%20a%20relatively%20recent%20invention%20in%20the%20history%20of%20human%20communication%2C%20as%20is%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Bhello%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fkrulwich%2F2011%2F02%2F17%2F133785829%2Fa-shockingly-short-history-of-hello%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThomas%20Edison%20encouraged%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20way%20to%20start%20a%20conversation%20on%20the%20new%20invention%20in%20the%201870s.%20Not%20until%20the%201940s%20did%20the%20majority%20of%20American%20households%20have%20their%20own%20phone.%20A%20whole%20new%20etiquette%20for%20handling%20phone%20calls%20has%20been%20invented%20within%20a%20generation%20or%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2204046d47-b6c4-4229-8600-84b973be71cd%5C%22%3ELandline%20phones%20had%20different%20customs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20elder%20millennial%2C%20I%20grew%20up%20with%20a%20home%20landline%20without%20caller%20ID%2C%20answering%20with%20variations%20of%2C%20%26quot%3BNotopoulos%20residence%2C%20this%20is%20Katie.%26quot%3B%20I've%20also%20had%20jobs%20with%20desk%20phones%20where%20strangers%20would%20call%20out%20of%20the%20blue%20(gasp!)%20and%20I%20would%20answer%20with%20the%20company%20name%2C%20my%20full%20name%2C%20maybe%20even%20a%20rote%20%26quot%3BHow%20can%20I%20help%20you%3F%26quot%3B%20Might%20we%20have%20possibly%20missed%20out%20on%20the%20Beastie%20Boys'%20album%20%26quot%3BHello%20Nasty%26quot%3B%20if%20not%20inspired%20by%20the%20way%20the%20receptionist%20at%20the%20Nasty%20Little%20Man%20PR%20firm%20answered%20the%20phone%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20within%20my%20(relatively)%20brief%20time%20as%20an%20adult%2C%20the%20way%20we%20use%20phones%20and%20what%20we%20do%20with%20them%20has%20changed%20drastically.%20Now%2C%20when%20you%20call%20someone%2C%20yo